{"/service/ndnp/txdn/batch_txdn_evans_ver01/data/sn86063730/00332894195/1930022002/0367.xml":{"full_text":"\u00ael* Hnmmsuflle Herald\nEstablished July 4, 1892\nEntered as second-class matter in the Poetofflce\nBrownsville Texas.\nTHE BROWNSVILLE HERALD PUBLISHING\nCOMPANY\nSubscription Rates\u2014Daily and Sunday Issues)\nOne Year .$9.00\nSix Months\nThree Months..\nOne Month. .75\nMEMBER OF THE ASSOCIATED PRESS\nThe Associated Press Is exclusively entitled to the use\nfor publication of all news dispatches credited to It or\nnot otherwise credited in this paper, and also the\nlocal news published herein.\nHarlingen Office. Reese-WU-Mond Hotel. Phone 1020\nTEXAS DAILY PRESS LEAGUE\nNational Advertising Representatives\nDallas. Texas, 512 Mercantile Bank Building.\nKansas City. Mo., 306 Coca Cola Building.\nChicago. 111., Association Building.\nNew York. 350 Madison Avenue.\n8t. Louis, 502 Star Building.\nLos Angeles. Cal., Room 1015 New Orpheum Bldg..\n646 8. Broadway.\nSan Francisco. Cal.. 318 Kohl Building.\nm-.\nMore Valley Transportation\nValley people are Inclined to underestimate the im\nportance of transportation to this section. By\ntransportation Is meant all means of travel and mov\ning commodities, by air, water, rail or highway.\nThe principal reason for losing sight of the Im\nportance of such facilities is the fact that the Valley\nhas so much to offer without the aid of adjoining\nsections.\nI But these adjoining sections will be all Important\nas the Valley develops.\nOil Is going to be produced in large quantities at\none or more points near the Valley. Geologists are\nconvinced that the field in Starr county, with one\nwell now producing, will be one of the largest in\nthe state.\nOil will be produced also In northern Mexico, at\none or more of the fields now being worked.\nOre Is mtned near Monterrey, and smelted there.\nAll northern Mexico is a rich country, which needs\nonly a few more years of stable government until\nIt will begin producing.\nThese commodities must move out to the mar\nkets of the world. As they are developed, it will\nmean that some point, through which they will move\nis to grow Into a city such as Houston or San An\ntonio.\nThe Lower Rio Grande Valley is the natural con\ncentration point for commodities of these adjacent\nterritories. The transportation facilities are being\nfurnished as rapidly as possible, and the day Is not\nfar distant when the big development from these\nsources will take place, to supplement the natural\nrichness of the Valley as an agricultural section, and\nIts growing attractions as a tourist resort.\nWe have now two eood railroad svstems, air trans\nportation with half a dozen airports of varying de\ngree of improvement, and a fairly good highway\nconnecting system with the outside world.\nThe next steps are being taken. Highways con\nnecting with points in Mexico, such as Monterrey.\nTampico, Mexico City, etc. Better rail connections\nwith Mexico. Water transportation. More highway\nconnections with the outside\u2014included In the Hug\nThe-Coast highway, and the river highway.\nThese improved means of transportation will make\na great metropolis out of the Valley, or some city in\nit. as the surrounding country' develops.\nAny money and effort spent now to Improve trans\nportation, such as the port work. Is well spent.\nCreed of the New Chief Justice\nChief Justice Charles Evans Hughes gave this defi\nnition of Christian character in a public address in\nthe remote past:\n\u201cFaith without* credulity, conviction without big\notry, charity without condescension, courage with\nout pugnacity, self respect without vanity, humility\nwithout obsequiousness, love of humanity without\naentimentallty and meekness with power. That is\nour Ideal.\"\nReally the definition reads like an excerpt from\na lay sermon by Former Oov. Pat Neff. It Is con\nceded that the former governor is a top notcher\nIn the ranks of word painters and phrase makers.\nThe Once Over\nBy EL L PHILLIPS\n11\n\u2022THE MARTIN JOHNSON JUNGLE INFLUENCE,\nOR WHY LIONS GO MAD.1\n(Copyright, 1830, by The Associated Newspapers.)\nL\nWhen the little baby lions are about to go to bed\nIn the very deepest jungles where the king of beasts\nis bred,\nMommer Lion and her husband warn the children in\na row\nOf the hunter and the huntress of the moving picture\nshow.\n\u201cOnce the jungle,\u201d so they tell them, \u201cwas a lovely\nplace to live,\nBut today a lion has to dodge the motor truck and\nfliv,\nAnd the menace he must watch for with his ears and\nnose and eyes.\nIs the rush of motor vehicles with camera supplies.\u201d\nn.\n\u201cOn the veldt,\u201d says Papa Lion, \"once a lion had\na chance\nAnd the life was fairly tranquil and a little like a\ntrance;\nNow and then a rifle crackled and a lion had to\njump,\nBut there weren\u2019t seven hunters to each tree and\nbush and clump.\nOh, today the life is awful and the strain is most\nintense\nFor the jungle\u2019s full of ladies and it\u2019s also full of\ngents\nWho are swarmin\u2019 through the grasses and are slog\nging through the bogs\nTo supply the picture houses with the Jungle travel\nogues.\nin.\n\u201cThere are clickings in the thicket, there are whir\nrings everywhere\nAs the motion picture crankers stir a tempest in the\nair;\nThere's a lens at every turning and outside of every\nlair\nThere's a Mr.-Mrs. Johnson or some other eager pair.\nIt's a life most photographic that the modem lion\nleads\nAs the tourists get the pictures for their tales of epic\ndeeds,\nAnd although there is less bloodshed in this very\nmodern day\nLions much prefer their shooting in the good old\nfashioned way.\nIV.\n\u201cWe are photographed when resting and we\u2019re pho\ntographed asleep.\nWe are snapped when we are eating and we're taken\nwhen we leap,\nWe are snapped when we are running and we\u2019re taken\nat a walk.\nAnd we know a lens is on us when we prowl and\nwhen we stalk.\nWe are photographed by dozens when we go to drink\na drink\nAnd we have our pictures taken when we even pause\nto think:\nWe are taken when we're angry and we\u2019re taken\nwhen we play\u2014\nAll we hear is cameras clicking every minute of the\ndav.\nV.\n\u201cFlivvers rattle all about us and we\u2019re very much an-\nnoyed\nAs the trucks go rumbling\u2014rumbling to the front\nwith celluloid:\nFor there's nothing makes a lion seem so much a\nhelpless ham\nAs to waste away of hunger caught within a traffic\nJam.\nSo. mv children, be as careful as you possibly can be\nIn a life in which you\u2019ll scarcely know the slightest\nprivacy;\nIf you hear a rifle cracking never make the slightest\nfuss.\nTake your bullet without flinching; it will be much\nbetter thus.\u2019\u2019\nADVERTISING\nYou kissed and told.\nBut that\u2019s all right:\nThe man you told\nCalled up last night.\n\u2014Pomona Sage Hen.\nI THE OLD HOME TOWN.Stanley\nr\\ knovnTotex^\nSOME galoot\nPOUPEP SOME ^__ ,T Ml^Hr\n\u25a0'LICKED /lAINT RPArriu'l DO FoR\nlOAL f ImT T O' CITY\n\u2022N TH' p?Jr np\u00b0^ATA BUT lTAINT\nfi?OOM BootlE<56EKS PTr\u00bbT 1\nAT NIQHT Stuff in TH\" g\u201eQLDA\nATE riMw- AT UflME JOOD\nTHIN<; Xnd durneo IF i^\\ T0NIc^C\n\"-\u201cONrWfTA V\n>^v h\u00b0uf,ana^ynk a r\nAS 8K5 AS MV W\n1\nTME Boon-EOGEfi^MARSHAL OTEy WALKER\nCAUGHT ON ICE HOUSE HILL WITH A BASKET\nOF SO CALLED *6000 STUFF? IS UNDER\nLOCK AND KEY\u2014NOW OTEY IS LOOKING FORA\nSAFE FIREPROOF CONTAINER FOR THETlCKERt.\ngl\u00bb\u00bba W. tTAWLgy CWTW L TW\u00ab_g -2>-'\u00bb0\nW.\u2014- I.\nCHAPTER 49\nAt that moment Pat and the\nDoctor rounded the corner of the\npilothouse. The former, evidently,\nhad caught the latter part of Mar\ngery\u2019s statement, for she glanced\nup at Rex with an inquiring look\nin her eyes.\n\"Don\u2019t you think it's a fine Idea.\nRex?\u201d she asked, a note of eager\nness in her voice. \u201cI\u2019ve Just been\ntelling Prank about it and he\nagrees that it certainly can do no\nharm and may be of wonderful\nbenefit! Talk to Jimmy, just as we\ndo to each other. There\u2019s no use.\nof course, to ask him questions. But\ntalk to him as if we thought he\nunderstood. Maybe he will\u2014after\nawhile. At any rate, it will seem\nmore human, more natural than\nto ignore him as we\u2019ve been doing!\u2019\u2019\ni inmic its a mighty good plan\n\u2014a whale of an idea!\" avowed Rex\nwith enthusiasm. Anything that\nPat sanctioned or wanted quite na\nturally had Dallard\u2019s unqualified\napproval at once. But this proposal\nhad struck him immediately as full\nof possibilities. Just the expression\non Jimmy\u2019s face that he had noted\nupon his approach the moment be\nfore was sufficient to warrant his\napproval of the plan.\nIt was an Interesting study to\nGordon, from both a personal and\na scientific viewpoint. Watching\nRex or Pat or anyone talking to\nJimmy, he was prone to wonder\nif. by any chance, the young man\ndid get a glimmer occasionally of\nwhat It was all about?\nWhether he did or whether he did\nnot. Pat and her friends continued\nto give him the \u201ctalk cure.\" Prob\nably. as Margery had said, he liked\nit. If he didn\u2019t, there was no indi\ncation on his part to show his dis\nlike. Nor was there anything to\nshow he did like it. It was Lucy\nPine who naively observed. \u201cJimmy\nhas the most detached manner 1\"\nIf complete Indifference to every\nthing and everybody around him\nwas the sign of \"detachment.\" then\nJimmy\u2019s manner was \"detached.\"\nDawn on the fifth day of the\ncruise saw the Bluebird's sharp\nprow cutting through the pirate\nfamed waters of the Caribbean Sea\nThe soft, warm air, laden with a\ntropical fragrance, breathed also\nthe romance and storied adventure\nthat had lived there in the days of\nMorgan and Capt. Kidd.\n\u201cI\u2019m perfectly sure.\u2019\u2019 declared Pat,\nstanding with Rex and Margery at\nthe port rail and looking ahead\nacross the green exnanse of ocean\ntoward the distant Barbados, \u201cthat\nif I\u2019d been Jimmy instead of being\nborn a girl, and had lived In the\nday When Knighthood Was in\nFlower, I should have been a fierce\n1 1\n\nFebruary 20, 1930\nWho am I? What Nebraska sen\nator opposed the confirmation ol\nthe appointment of my father's\nsuccessor recently? What was m>\nmother's maiden name?\nWhat comet is due to return\nabout 1985?\nTo what church was Benjamin\nDisraeli, England's great prime\nminister, admitted after the death\nof his father?\n\"Salt is good: but If the salt have\nlost his savour, wherewith shall it\nbe seasoned?\" Where is this pass\nage found In the Bible?\nCorrectly Speaking\u2014\nWhen two or more singular sub\njects are joined #by (or) or (nor) a\nsingular verb Is required. Say\n\u201cNeither he nor she is going.\" not\n\"Neither he nor she are going.\"\nToday\u2019s Anniversary\nOn this day. in 1829. the Ameri\ncan actor, Joseph Jefferson, was\nborn.\nToday\u2019s Horoscope\nPersons born on this day are\nfaithful workers and give more\nthan is expected of them.\nAnswers to Foregoing Questions\n1. Robert Tait; George W. Nor\nris: Helen Herron.\n2. Halley s.\n3. Church of England.\n4. St. Luke, xiv, 34.\nStar Lore\nATTRACTIVE OBJECTS IN FEB\nRUARY EVENING SKY\nBy Arthur DeV. Carpenter\nCapella is now overhead a little\nwest of the meridian, and is next\nto Sirius the brighest star visible\nin February. Its magnitude Is 0.21.\nZero is the next magnitude brighter\nthan the first magnitude. This star\nis often called \u201cGolden Capella\"\nbecause It shines with a rich yel\nlow light. This is a good month for\nseeing the constellation Cancer\n(Crab), located between Gemini\nand Leo. Cancer is famous for its\ncluster of more than 300 stars too\nfaint to be distinguished with the\nraked eye. but all of them together\nform a patch of radiant light Just\nvisible on very clear, moonless\nnights. Be sure to locate It.\n(More Tomorrow)\nbuccaneer! Just fancy the wild,\nfree life!\n\"A-ya, fancy it!\u201d yawned Rex un\nfeelingly. \u201cJust fancy it that's\nenough! The free life of cutthroats\nand scalawags! Where can you\nfind anything in the stories of those\ndays to equal the perfected products\nof tha present day\u2014a yacht like\nthis, for instance?\u201d\n\u2018\u2018Well,\u201d conceded Pat magnani\nmously, \"you're probably right.\nMuch of the splendor and glory at\ntributed to the old buccaneer days,\nI suppose, would be tinsel and\nwhitewash in the golden realities\nof the 20th Century!\u201d\nThe course steered by Captain\nLee had been almost due south\nfrom New York, the yacht passing\nDetween Porto Rico and Jamaica,\nInto the Caribbean. The Itinerary\nplanned by Pat and her friends\nwould take them past the Barbados\nto Trinidad, thence around the\nEast coast of South America to Rio\nde Janeiro, Buenos Aires, down\nthrough the strait of Magellan and\nthen up through the South Pacific\nto San Francisco. That had been\nthe route planned.\nThe yacht had been running all\nday under greatly reduced speed.\nThis was owing to the more or less\ndangerous course lying between the\nwest passage of Jamaica and the\nBarbados. This course, Captain Lee\nexplained, was noted for Its many\nugly coral reefs that lay hidden\nbeneath the water's surface. In\ngood weather, when there w\u2019as no\nsea running, the danger was great\nly obviated, although navigators\nnever overlooked the need of cau\ntious navigation.\nDuring the day the yacht passed\nwithin a few miles of several is\nlands, all small, but covered with\na profuse tropical growth.\nJust after the dinner gong sound\ned, and as Margery and Pat, walk\ning a few feet ahead of Rex and\nthe doctor, were about to enter\nthe doorway leading to the main\ncabin, the squat figure of th* red\nheaded deckhand suddenly rounded\nthe corner of the pilot house. He\nseemed at the same instant to\ncatch sight of the two girls, for he\nwhirled as though on a pivot ;nd\ndarted back in the direction from\nwhich he had come.\nBut in that instant Margery had\nobtained a full look at him. On\nthis occasion her memory perform- t\ned its duty. She knew then where\nshe had seen those piggy eyes a id\nthat surly, cruel mouth before. It i\nhad been the scrubby moustache\nhe had grown that had prevented\nher recognition of him that day\nat the dock.\n\u201cHah!\u201d The ejaculation leaped\nfrom her lips. She. too, whirled\nfacing her friends, her arm raid\u2019d\nin a theatrical gesture, command\ning attention.\nDia you see thru man just 'ncn'\nshe cried excitedly, her eyes wide\nwith a sudden, rew-born fear. The\nfellow\u2019s motions had been so sw ft\nthat he might have escaped the\nether\u2019s sight. But he hadn't, as it\nhappened. They had all seen him\nThey stared at her wonderingiy.\n\u201cI just recognized him!'' she went\non in a tragic, husky half-whisper.\n\u2022\u2022It's the roughneck that black\njacked me that day\u2014the brute who\nknocked poor Jimmy down. What\n\u2014oh what do you suppose, is he\ndoing, or planning to do here? It\ncan\u2019t be simply coincidence! That\nman is a hireling of Maxwell! He's\naboard this yacht for some evil\npurpose\u2014to kill Jimmv, most like\nly! What shall we do?\u2019*\nThe ominous portent embodied in\nMargerv\u2019s startling declaration was\nunmistakable. F wer* facts and\nthere was no rTTTTTng them. This\nman was a Maxwell agent. He could\nbe on board this yacht for no oth\ner purpose than to do Maxwell's\ndirtv work!\n\u2022\u2019We must notify the Captain at\nonce!\u201d announced Rex Dallard with\na grim seriousness. \u2018The fellow\u2019s\nverv presence here bespeaks a plot\nof Maxwells hatching! He must be\nput off the yacht at the very earl\niest opportunity! In the meantime\nhe should be locked up! Wed bet\nter see the Captain right away!\u201d\nThey met Captain Lee at the\nhead of the staircase as he was\ncoming down from the pilothouse\non the ship\u2019s officers, at the spec\nific request of Pat. ate with the\nowner and her guests. Private\nyacht etiquette differs ordinarily\nfrom that maintained aboard pas\nsenger vessels, where It is consider\ned an honor to be invited to sit at\nthe captain\u2019s table.\nRex Dallard lost no time in mak\ning Captain Lee acquainted with\nthe facts concerning the deck\nhand whom Margery had just re\ncognized and the positive menace\nthat his presence aboard the yacht\npresaged. He went on still further,\npointing out to the captain the\nabsolute necessity of making it im\npossible for the man to work any\nfell design by locking him up se\ncurely until they reached some\nport, where the fellow could be put\nashore.\n\u201cYou understand, of course. Cap\ntain.*\u2019 continued Rex, \u201cthat we\nwould not ask you to act in this\nradical manner unless we were ab\nsolutely certain the facts in the case\nwarrant extreme measures. There\nis no chance that we are making\nSAMBO\u2019S PHILOSOPHY\n_\n\u201cOr Nlggah Jim all lamed np to\ninv. Big piece of white papnn\n\u2022\u2022lowed outen de graveyabd at *im\nwhilst he passin\u2019 dor las\u2019 night**\nPULLING ANOTHER WILD ONE\ndiverting \\V/(fl\nBUT NOTVFRn VX^\n\u2122*iN(;y 'oJ\nr\nTUP\nCOUNTRY\nmistake. This man Is hireling of\nMaxwell's and his presence here\ncan be for no other purpose than\nto do Maxwell's bidding! When you\nconsider that the sum of money In\nvolved totals fourteen million dol\nlars, you will realize the need for\nthe precautions I am urging!\u2019*\n*\u2018I realize it fully. Mh. Dallard,\u201d\nCaptain Lee assured him. \u2019\u2019And I\ngive you my word\u2014all of you\u2014\u201d\nHe included the three others in a\nsweeping gesture, \u201cthat I shall act\nimmediately. Within ten minutes\nthe ma:i will be securely confined\nin the yacht\u2019s strong room!\"\n(TO BE CONTINUED)\nTEXAS\nTOPICS\n\u2014Familiar Scenes\n\u2014Marlin Gavel\n\u2014No-Par Stock\n\u2014(And Less Cotton\nAUSTIN, Feb. 20\u2014\u2019Jimmie,\u201d oth\nerwise James V. Allred of Wichita\nFails, told friends he will be the\n\u201cpeople's lawyer,\u201d as attorney gen\neral. if elected in his race this year.\nHe found friends and many ac\nquaintances her during a visit, and\nhe demonstrated he already is in\nhigh gear for a handshaking cam\npaign.\n\nJudge W. H. Woodward of Cole\nman is here visiting his son. Sen.\nWalter C. Woodward.\n\nWayne Somerville, county attor\nney of Wichita county, was among\nthe public officials here during the\nweek to confer with the home\ntown representatives and other of\nthe legislators.\n\n\u201cBig John\u201d Davis, former house\nand senate member from Dallas,\nmingled with old-time associates\nabout the corridors this week. His\nnickname came from the fact that\nthere were two John Davises, both\nfrom Dallas, in the legislature at\nthe same time, and from the further\nfact that is around six feet six\ninches tall.\n\nFormer AdJ. Gen. James A. Har\nley was among the numerous law\nyers who gathered around the com\nmittee tables during the past sev\neral days as tax questions were\ntackled.\n\nRep. Harold Kayton holds the\npalm for the best-scrambled figure\nof speech of the session.\n\u201cDo they want to make a goo\nout of us to wash their dirty lin\nen?\" he demanded indignantly oi\na committee.\nt\nJack Johnson of Denton is an\nother of the old-time members whe\nhave rallied \u2018round the capitol wher\nthe legislative sawmill got to\ngrinding, late in the session.\n\nDayton Moses has a breathing\nspell as he waits for the postponed\ni ATTENTION?!\nx We have added a\nt Rental Library to our\nI store! Come in and look\nit over. All of the best I\nsellers of all publishers, f\nKeep abreast of the\nx most popular new books 2\nt by renting them at\nf small cost!\nHARGROVE\u2019S|;\nI Stationery Book Store\nL Phone 348\nBrownsville, Texas 1\nFEED GRAIN\nAND\nHAY\nMcLELLAND FEED CO..\nPh;je 765 508 N. Commerce\nHarlinfen\ni hi\nvenue hearing in the case of his\nclient, Judge John W. Brady.\n\nReno Eiclcenroht of Seguin. only\nrepublican house member, will have\na good excuse'to be absent Sat\nurday, with his party's state execu\ntive committee meeting in Sen.\nThomas B. Love's home city.\n\nGen. Jacob F. Wolters. the man\nthey turn to when there's to be\nmartial law, has been beneath the\nbig dome for several days, quietly\nwatching the trend of legislative ef\nfort. Esteem in which he is held\nby the lawmakers was reflected in\nresolutions thanking him for nls\nservices at Borger in conducting the\nmartial law administration.\nm m m\nCol. Abe Cross, of Waco, who\ncame about his title as a member\nof a governors staff, mixes with\nthe business representatives here\nwho consider certain business taxes\npoisonous.\n\nTalk about quiet firmness. Rep.\nVictor Gilbert, who is chairman of\nthe revenue and taxation commit*\ntee, sat till after midnight In tha\nsulphur tax hearing. Finally Mr.\nGilbert announced, as members\nkept on debating. \u201cI'm going to put\nthe motion now\u2019\u2014you fellows are out\nof order.\u201d And he did.\nAll his committee has to do is to\nraise money by tax measures: all\nRep. John F. Wallace's committee\nhas to do is to spend it. yet It\nw\u2019ould be hard to guess which of the\ntwo has the hardest Job\u2014both are\ntold \u201cthere isn't any\u201d to raise or\nto spend.\nA. TAMM\nBlue Printing and\nSupplies\nHarlingen, Texas\n1911 1910\nSkelton Abstract Co.\nAbstracts of Title Title Insurance\nMerchants Bank Building Brownsville\nCARNEIRO, CHUMNEY COMPANY\nCertified Public Accountants\nIncome Tax Service\nBROWNSVILLE SAN ANTONIO CORPUS rHRISTI\nState National Banl. Smith-Young Tower Nixon Build tag\n-PR SPERITY T\nProsperity for Brownsville and\nthe Valley is a tangible, able-to\ni>e-seen condition. Citrus groves\nire beginning to bloom vege\ntables are commanding good\nprices generally the interna\ntional airport and the bright\n>rospects for a deep water port\u2014\nall are encouraging a splendid\nbusiness outlook for Brownsville\nand the Valley.\nLet us, as your bank, help\nyou with any problems you\nmay wish to discuss with us.\nFirst National Bank\nEstablished in 1891\nBROWNSVILLE, TEXAS\nTITLE INSURANCE\nWhen you borrow money on real estate, many loan companies re\nquire the title to be insured. The best test of whether a Ulie M\ninsurable, is to have it insured. Require a title insurance policy\nwhen you buy.\nVALLEY ABSTRACT COMPANY\nPrompt Title Service\nBrownsville Fdinhurc\nOpposite Court House C. iiarriman Blvd.\nPhone 1184 Phone 93","height":"36644","width":"27752"}}
